UK Labour 2 - 7 fav to win Wirral by - election . British bookmakers City Index said on Monday they rated Labour 2 - 7 favourites to win the Wirral South parliamentary by - election , taking place on February 27 . The ruling Conservatives , who are defending the seat , are rated 9 - 4 and the Liberal Democrats 66 - 1 . The Wirral South seat was held by the Conservatives with a majority of more than 8 , 000 at the 1992 election . The by - election was triggered by the death of MP Barry Porter . A weekend opinion poll said 54 percent of the vote in the north - west England constituency would go to Labour , 35 percent to the Conservatives and 10 percent to the Liberal Democrats . 
